# Wedding Card UI Clone Implementation Plan

We will build a pixel-perfect, responsive clone of the provided wedding invitation website using a modern stack: **React (via Vite) and Tailwind CSS**. This ensures the smooth animations, frosted glass effects, and exact typography are seamlessly replicated.

## User Review Required

> [!NOTE]
> Please review this plan. If you approve, I will automatically initialize the project in your `WeddingCard` folder and build out all the files.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The original site uses custom SVG line-art flowers in the corners. I will create visually similar CSS/SVG placeholders for these. If you have the exact SVG files later, they can be easily swapped in.

## Proposed Changes

We will initialize a new React project in the current directory and implement the following structure:

### 1. Project Setup
- Generate a standard React template using Vite.
- Install Tailwind CSS and its dependencies.
- Add Framer Motion for smooth scroll and entry animations (replicating the "Next.js hydrating" feel).

### 2. Global Styling & Configuration

#### [MODIFY] `index.html`
- Import Google Fonts: `Cormorant Garamond` (weights 400, 500, 600) and `Montserrat` (weights 300, 400, 500).

#### [MODIFY] `tailwind.config.js`
- Set up custom color palette:
  - `wedding-bg`: `#F5F4F0` (Cream)
  - `wedding-green`: `#6B8E6B` (Sage text/SVG)
  - `wedding-green-light`: `#E8F0E8` (RSVP button bg)
  - `wedding-red-light`: `#FCE8E8` (Decline button bg)
  - `wedding-red`: `#D9534F` (Decline text)
- Add custom font families (`cormorant`, `montserrat`).

#### [MODIFY] `index.css`
- Implement the global grain/noise overlay using an SVG data-URI filter to achieve the premium textured background look.

### 3. React Components

#### [NEW] `src/App.jsx`
- The main wrapper. It will manage the full-screen fixed background (cream + noise) and the central, centered layout container for the `Card`.

#### [NEW] `src/components/WeddingCard.jsx`
- The core glassmorphic container (`bg-white/95 backdrop-blur-xl rounded-xl shadow-2xl`). It will be vertically scrollable with hidden scrollbars for a clean look.

#### [NEW] `src/components/TopHero.jsx`
- The top section featuring the star icon, "We Can't Wait!", the couple's names in large `Cormorant` font, and the general invitation text.

#### [NEW] `src/components/EventDetails.jsx`
- A split layout or simple stacked layout showing:
  - Date (14 April, 04 PM)
  - Venue (Malabar Marina) with a location button.
  - "Click here for location" button mimicking the pill-shape UI.

#### [NEW] `src/components/Countdown.jsx`
- The 4-box layout displaying Days, Hours, Mins, Secs. Clean white boxes with inner shadows.

#### [NEW] `src/components/RSVPSection.jsx`
- Contains the "Will you attend?" prompt and the two large, bordered selection cards (Yes / No).
- Includes the bottom "Edit Response" sticky button.

## Verification Plan

### Automated/Manual Verification
- Once built, I will run `npm run dev` and use the background browser tool to snap a screenshot of our running clone so we can compare it side-by-side with the original site screenshots.
